![](/static/Fullstack.png)
# FullStack Architecture

Every three seconds a new website is built. The average reading speed can range between 200 to 250 words per minute. Assuming you can read up to 300 words per minute then by the time you finish reading this article about 240 websites can be created.

Globally, 71% of businesses have a website in 2023. More than 28% of businesses conduct their online activities and more than 43% of small businesses are planning to invest in their website performance.

According to GoDaddy Data Observatory India 2023, it shows that 55% of small businesses have been launched in the last five years and 62% of
Indian small businesses have a website,e-commerce platform or an online store as their main source of sales channel to grow their business.
In the past five years, 83% of small businesses started selling online and 65% of small businesses make up to 50% of revenue from online sales.

Mobile phones are still 46% of the relevant mode for most people in India.

With the increasing reliance on web-based applications across industries, the demand for skilled full stack developers is at an all-time high. Organizations are constantly seeking individuals who can handle end-to-end development, offering lucrative career prospects and ample job opportunities in the tech sector.

By mastering both front-end and back-end technologies, full stack developers gain a comprehensive understanding of the entire development process. This holistic perspective enables them to architect robust solutions, optimize performance, and troubleshoot issues effectively, ultimately delivering better products to end-users.


![](/static/FullStack_Technologies.png)

### Prerequisites to Getting into Full Stack Development
1. Knowledge Of Any Object Oriented Language with DSA skill
2. Creativity
3. Problem Solving Skill
4. Continuous Learning Attitude
5. CS Fundmentals (Good to have)

blogs.content:
# Data Science Prerequisites

![](/static/DS_MLRelationship.webp)

Data science stands at the intersection of mathematics, statistics, artificial intelligence, and computer engineering, offering a multidisciplinary approach to extracting meaningful insights from vast datasets. By employing advanced tools and techniques, data scientists delve into the depths of data to uncover answers to critical questions such as what happened, why it happened, what will happen next, and what actions can be taken based on the findings.

In today's digital age, data science plays a pivotal role in deciphering the ever-increasing volume of data generated by modern organizations. From e-commerce transactions to medical records and financial transactions, data permeates every aspect of human life. This abundance of data presents both challenges and opportunities for businesses seeking to derive actionable insights to drive decision-making processes.

![](/static/ML_AI_DL_Relationship.webp)

## Prerequisites for Learning Data Science
1. Knowledge Of Any Object Oriented Language with DSA skill
2. Knowledge of 12th Class Mathematics like Linear Algebra, Statistics, Calculus.
3. Problem Solving Skill & Analytical Thinking
4. Knowledge of CS Fundmentals is Must and Should
5. Web Application Knoweldge is Not Mandatory But Good To have

## History of Modern Computer Science

 ![](/static/AlanTuringQuote.jpg)

Alan Turing was considered the Father of Modern-Day Computer Science while working for the British Secret Service during World War II. Turing was recruited, along with a few other mathematicians, into the code-breaking effort undertaken by the British government at Bletchley Park to crack the Enigma machine. The Enigma was a sophisticated electro-mechanical device used by the German military to encrypt their orders, including those transmitted to the U-boats wreaking havoc on the Atlantic shipping lanes. The ‚Äúkeys‚Äù - the sets of rules for encoding messages - used by the Enigma would change constantly. Turing designed machines, known as ‚Äúbombes‚Äù, that could cycle through hundreds and thousands of Enigma settings to match the available ‚Äúcribs‚Äù (the most frequently occurring words across messages) to identify the correct key. It was extremely difficult work, tense and taut, equal parts educated guesswork and puzzle solving. Turing's contributions helped make the decryption work at Bletchley Park a success and played a substantial role in the eventual victory of the Allies over Axis Powers, leading to the foundation of Computer Science after the war. You can learn more about this invention in the documentary film called The Imitation Game. You can learn about this theoretically from a subject called Theory Of Computation in more detail.

 ## Early Age Computers 
 ![](/static/EarlyComputers.jpg)

- The Early Age Computers are Very large in Size, The cost of Memory and Processor is also high
- Early Age Computers are mainly used for Scientific and Industrial Purpose.

In 1984 Apple Company released 1st version of Personal computer Macintosh,Modern day Computers,Laptops evolved from this Machine Steve Jobs and Steve Wozniac together developed this,So that Common man can use it for personal purpose.

 ## Programming a Computer

There are a plethora of languages that the programmer uses for giving commands to the computer. All these languages are categorized as assembly-level language, machine-level language, and high-level language. Languages like C, C++, Python, and Java are high-level programming languages. Machine-level language is a low-level language that deals with 0s and 1s, Whereas assembly-level language lies between low-level language and high-level language; it is more of an intermediary language.
